@tara_shreve Hi! 
I'm sorry you feel that way about our service.  If you would like to submit your comments or complaints, please contact our Customer Care department.
https://t.co/OzrIxYNv63 and select "General Complaint or compliment".

//Best regards, Dennis

@marcnoruega Hej! 
Ja man kan ändra information för en resenär på en biljett men då behöver man ringa vår kundtjänst, du kan ringa dom på +47 2189 6400 så kan dom hjälpa er kolla på hur det skulle bli med kostnader osv.

//Vänlig hälsning, Dennis.

@acertainellen Hey!
Please contact us on our live chat so my colleagues can check this out.
Whit kind regards Liv.

@anna_hernandez1 Hi! 
Contact us on our live chat and we will help you.
With kind regards Liv.

@monnikje Hello
Yes maybe you need to like or follow the page , you can also contact us by live chat https://t.co/b3QIqPBI2R
Best regards /Anna

@monnikje Hello
Since the refund is made to the same voucher that was used the expire date is also the same , we may be able to extend it. It depends on when it expired , contact us on messenger and we will at least see if it is possible.
Best regards /Anna

@monnikje Hello
Refund is made to the original form of payment. If you have used a voucher on a ticket and then request refund the refund will be made to the same voucher that was used. 

Best regards /Anna

@walk_maryanne Hi Mary Anne
You can contact our head office on phone +46 8 797 0000

Best regards /Anna

@b_jackson__ Hi! If you want to leave your comments or complaints, you can contact our Customer Care department.
You can contact them here via this link:
https://t.co/OzrIxYNv63 select "General Complaint or compliment". Kind regards, Jonna.

@jztlikehvn Hello, we unfortunately don't have any information on when personal items will be allowed in the cabin again. The current restrictions lasts until further notice.

Best regards,
Anton.

@ManniGee1971 Hello, you can find our phone numbers on https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj by selecting your region and then clicking on "Customer Service / Eurobonus".

Best regards,
Anton.

@jawst97 Hi @jawst97,
Go to https://t.co/ui2Ls6yWKm and "Check Voucher Balance". When your voucher has expired, you can claim a refund there.
Best regards, Mikael.

@NiaMoore93 You can contact us on live-chat or Messenger with the SAS booking reference and we can take a look, if we are not able to see the refund status you will have to contact the travel agency where you booked the ticket.

Best regards,
Anton.

@DevsFaye07 Hello,
Please contact our customer service and we will inform you about how to add your extra luggage. You can contact us via this link: https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj
Kind regards, Anja

@OnlySeverinsen Hej, 
Du kan efterregistrera poängen via https://t.co/kFAspOYqMD upp till 6 månader efter resan. Vid problem att efterregistrera poängen är du välkommen att kontakta vår kundjänst så hjälper vi dig. Du kan kontakta oss via denna länk: https://t.co/cIkJt9kPnF
Hälsningar Anja

@djfgiugno Hi! 
Yes a 14 year old can travel by himself if he is comfortable with that, there may be rules regarding minors traveling alone so i recommend that you check that with the embassy for the country he is traveling to.

//Best regards, Dennis.

@djfgiugno Hi
That was strange. We reply on messenger usually the same day but sometimes the day after. 
Best regards /Anna

@djfgiugno Hello Jacqueline
The chats are handled in the order received so don't worry, you will be connected when it is your turn. You can also contact us by messenger but we may not respond immediately so if it is more urgent matter I recommend live chat.
Best regards /Anna

@Haynala Hi
You do not receive a new voucher, the refund is made to the same voucher so you can use it again as soon as refund is done.

Best regards/ Anna

@Haynala Hello
The refund is made to the original form of payment. If you have used a voucher it will be refunded to the same voucher. You can read about 24 hour money back guarantee via this link https://t.co/Nq4vJOQB0l

Best regards /Anna

@paquillomartin Hi paquillomartin, we recommend that you delete this tweet as we do not recommend that you share your booking reference online, Please contact us at Customer Service at the following link and we will look in to your errand. 
https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Kind regards, Isak

@Nadia_R_Thorius Hello Nadja, thank you for contacting us.
SAS as a company does not require a test for the traveler to travel with us, but the staff at the airport will check your travel documents and any test results if the country you are traveling to requires this. 
Kind regards, Anja

@Haynala Hello, thank you for contacting us.
Yes, it's going great. The voucher is not personal, so if you know someone who wants to fly, they can use your voucher.
Kind regards, Anja.

@Steffo737 Ja vi kommer att återgå till ordinarie serviceutbud när pandemin är över, begränsningar och ändringar i vår service är bara tillfälligt under pandemin.

Med vänlig hälsning,
Anton.

@Steffo737 Hej! Vi har valt att göra ändringar i vår service ombord för att underlätta resandet och minska smittspridning under pandemin. Du kan läsa mer om vilka åtgärder vi tagit här https://t.co/RWpVwLQoMq

Med vänlig hälsning,
Anton.

@vazzer Hello! Please contact us on FB Messenger or live-chat with the details of your refund notice and we will help you take a look at that.

Best regards,
Anton.

@AndreasAasheim Hei! 
Jag beklagar att din resa vart ändrad. I det fallet rekommenderar jag att du ringer vår kundeservice på +47 2189 6400 så kan vi hjälpa dig kolla på andra alternativ att boka om till.

//Vänlig hälsning, Dennis.

@JoramLangbroek Hi! 
It should be possible to cancel a trip on our website and request a voucher, but in some cases that is not possible and then you will have to contact our customer service to request that voucher. We apologize for the inconvenience.

//Best regards, Dennis.

@becomegreennow Hi again, then please contact us at Customer Service at the following link,
https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Kind regards, Isak

@becomegreennow Hi Becomegreennow, please contact us at Customer Service on the following link or over Facebook Messenger so we can have a look in to your errand,
https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Kind regards, Isak

@pilegaard Hello, thank you for contacting us!

I am terribly sorry for the long wait. Kindly contact us via our chat support and we will take a look at this for you. https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Kind regards, Anja

@LinneaSchossow Hi Linnea!

If you arrive on an international flight and your bag tags show that you will continue your trip on a domestic flight on SAS, your bags will be checked through to your final destination.

Kind regards, Christoffer

@EmiliaWiden Hello, I'm terribly sorry to hear that you were not let on the flight! I recommend that you open a claim with our Customer Care department regarding the refund https://t.co/wprQ9Zejqh

Best regards,
Anton.

@lillsnor Hello. You can bring your drone as carry-on as long as it does not exceed max weight or size for carry-on baggage and does not contain lithium batteries exceeding an effect of 160W. Batteries must be individually protected to prevent short circuits.

Best regards,
Anton.

@Queen_beefly Hello! Your boarding pass will be created when you check-in. Either printed in physical form at the self-service machine on the airport or in the smartphone app depending on how you choose to check-in. Online check in opens 30h before departure.

Best regards,
Anton.

@huey_bb Hey!
Contact us on our live chat and we will review your booking and refund.
With kind regards Liv

@sam_fowler_97 Okay I am sorry to hear that the problem still persists. In this case you have to call us on the phone to pay for the seating. You can find our phone numbers here https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Best regards,
Anton.

@sam_fowler_97 Hello, could you please try clearing cache and cookies in your web browser to see if that helps? Also make sure the card you are using is open for internet purchases.

Best regards,
Anton.

@marsden_paula Hello, I'm sorry to hear that you've been sent in circles regarding you refund errand. Could you please provide us your booking details via the Facebook Messenger app so I can take a look at this for you?

Best regards,
Anton.

@dieterdieter15 Hello, please contact us on Facebook Messenger or live-chat with the voucher number so we can take a look to see if the voucher is refundable.

Best regards,
Anton.

@lynnehooper18 Hello, I'm sorry to hear that your luggage was damaged. This has to be reported with Baggage Service on the airport within 7 days of the discovery of the damage. I'm sorry for the inconvenience but this can not be reported online.

Best regards,
Anton.

@HannahPa1 Hi HannahPa1, You can login and change email under "My Eurobonus" and settings or contact us at either Facebook Messenger or Customer Service on the following link and we will help you in your errand,
https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Kind regards, Isak

@walterp_tv Hi! 
That depends on where and when you want to fly. You can see our prices here: https://t.co/aWeTBFSc4C

//Best regards, Dennis.
